data.name: Pesto Pasta
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick and flavorful pasta dish tossed in fresh basil pesto, perfect for a busy weeknight meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Boil a large pot of salted water and cook the pasta according to package instructions until al dente.
While the pasta is cooking, in a large mixing bowl, combine the pesto sauce and olive oil.
Once the pasta is cooked, reserve 1/2 cup of pasta water, then drain the pasta.
Add the hot pasta to the bowl with pesto and mix well. If the pasta seems dry, add a bit of the reserved pasta water until desired consistency is reached.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm, garnished with extra Parmesan cheese if desired.
